<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ROYAL-STALLS-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DECORATED HORSE STALLS AT AMERICAN ROYAL EARN PRAISE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JERRY BERRIOS  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Juel Carman might be the Martha Stewart of
horse shows. But he wrinkles his nose at that description.
</P>
<P>
   Carman, after all, is a hired gun _ staple gun that is.
</P>
<P>
   Carman, 64, decorates stalls at about 20 horse shows across the
country. This week he brought his talent with bolts of cheesecloth
to the American Royal. Carman has decorated horse stalls at the
American Royal for about 33 years.
</P>
<P>
   By last Tuesday afternoon, Carman and his five-man crew had
decorated 300 stalls in three days. They used 100,000 staples and
between 4,000 and 5,000 yards of cheesecloth _ imagine about two to
three miles of cloth.
</P>
<P>
   Owners tell Carman what colors to use, usually the farm or
stable's colors, and what kind of design they want.
</P>
<P>
   Carter Cox, the owner of Woodstock Farm in Danville, Ky., said
Carman has decorated his stalls at the American Royal for about 16
years. Cox said presentation is important.
</P>
<P>
   Cox said he will spend between $1,500 and $2,000 on the 10
stalls Carman decorated this year.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you are going to sell a Mercedes there has to be a certain
imagery to it,'' Cox said. ``I think Juel helps project that.''
</P>
<P>
   Carman weaves his magic with his trusty staple gun and colorful
cloth. A gray rosette here. A red, gray and black sunburst there.
Or maybe a simple front of blue and gray.
</P>
<P>
   He decorates horse stalls, tack rooms, sitting rooms and stall
fronts.
</P>
<P>
   Carman started in the decorating business with his father-in-law
in 1966.
</P>
<P>
   Horse show veterans say Carman has cornered the market.
</P>
<P>
   ``Juel pretty well has a monopoly,'' Cox said.
</P>
<P>
   But Carman insists, ``It's open to anyone who wants to work.''
</P>
<P>
   Maybe Stewart needs a challenge.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
