Celebration Services, Smith has coordinated many elegant and
creative affairs. We sat down with Smith at her to ask for tips in
planning an upcoming
</P>
<P>
   holiday bash. (Moss, Dayton Daily News). 21. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   KIDPARTY _ You don't have to wait for a birthday to throw a
children's party. Why not plan one in honor of the millennium or an
upcoming holiday? A kid's event can be educational, entertaining
and fun. (Moss, Dayton Daily News). 11. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   PARTYMENU _ It would take a scholar to come up with a millennium
menu for a holiday party. But a ``Century Party'' is another thing.
And you've got just seven weeks to have it before the opportunity
fades forever. Consider a cocktail party with signature dishes from
all 10 decades. (Heller, Dayton Daily News). 28. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
