</P>
<P>
   POZCOL. Joe Posnanski column on K-State vs. Nebraska and all the
little towns between Lincoln, Neb., and Manhattan, Kan.
</P>
<P>
   KSNEB13. It's the Black Shirts vs. the Purple Tide. The
trademark of these two teams are the defenses. Kansas State may
have the most dominant defense in the conference. But it needs to
avoid the big plays that it gave up against Colorado last Satrday.
Kent Pulliam. 18.
</P>
<P>
   FIGHT13. Evander Holyfield is looking tired these days. His
speech is slurred, his punches slower. That much was very clear the
last time Holyfield stepped into the ring and fought Lennox Lewis
to unify the heavyweight title. Lennox outpointed the courageous
champion and then was promptly robbed of the decision. So
Holyfield, who has risen to the challenge so many times before in
his career, must prove himself again tonight in the Las Vegas
rematch. David Boyce. 18-20.
</P>
<P>
   ROYALS. Updater on the Royals' ownership situation. Steve Rock.
</P>
<P>
   THOMAS. Quietly, Derrick Thomas is having a good season for the
Chiefs. Playing back as a linebacker again, Thomas is pressuring
quarterbacks again and having fun. Randy Covitz. 16-18. Photos
</P>
<P>
   KUFT. Advance on Kansas at Oklahoma State. The Jayhawks look to
end their road woes and eliminate the Cowboys from bowl
consideration. Bob Dutton. 12.
</P>
<P>
   MUFT: University of Missouri football advance for Texas A&AMP;M.
Mike DeArmond. 12.
</P>
