72-year-old trick roper, has been on the road, hauling a horse and
trailer. He has twirled ropes for presidents, singers, movie stars
and a queen, and he once got a glimpse of a goddess. Now, he's
alongside Roy Rogers, Gene Autry, Hopalong Cassidy and other cowboy
entertainers in the National Cowboy Hall of Fame in Oklahoma City.
``I feel it's the highest honor you can have,'' said Stoker, who
was inducted Oct. 17. By JEFF PRINCE. Story has moved in ``l''
