   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   WARSH-COLUMN (Undated) _ One of the most curious phenomena on
the political landscape is Steve Forbes' presidential campaign. The
New Jersey Republican has spent $60 million to $75 million of his
own money in four years, with little to show for it but a 5 percent
or so standing in the polls. By David Warsh.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCE-HOOKER (Undated) _ Senior worker may want to bump up
fixed-income holdings. By Kenneth Hooker.
</P>
