   No. 19 Clemson (5-4)
</P>
<P>
   at No. 22 Georgia Tech (6-2)
</P>
<P>
   Tech is averaging 507.8 yards a game and Clemson gained 558 last
week.
</P>
<P>
   No. 14 Louisiana Tech (7-2)
</P>
<P>
   at Alabama-Birmingham (4-5)
</P>
<P>
   Tim Rattay, Tech's passing star, faces a difficult defense.
</P>
<P>
   Auburn (4-5)
</P>
<P>
   at Georgia (6-2)
</P>
<P>
   Georgia may have trouble rushing against this defense.
</P>
<P>
   MIDWEST
</P>
<P>
   No. 17 Michigan State (7-2)
</P>
<P>
   at Northwestern (3-6)
</P>
<P>
   An easy one for Michigan State's defense, which held Ohio State
to 79 yards.
</P>
<P>
   No. 18 Marshall (9-0)
</P>
<P>
   at Western Michigan (7-2)
</P>
<P>
   Marshall, sure to reach the Motor City Bowl, wants a bigger one.
</P>
<P>
   Indiana (4-5)
</P>
<P>
   at No. 21 Minnesota (6-3)
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota is reveling in its first winning season since 1990.
</P>
<P>
