<SLUG> BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, Nov. 13. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
AUTO-REVIEW (Phoenix) - Driving all kinds of different vehicles can
cause unexpected problems. Such as confronting a vast parking lot,
when I have to stop and ask myself not only where did I park but
what did I park.
</P>
<P>
   Not a problem with the new Ford Excursion. A true behemoth, the
Excursion is the world's biggest sport-utility vehicle, somewhat
dwarfing the erstwhile holder of the claim, Chevrolet Suburban, and
making Ford's former big dog, the Expedition, look like a shrinking
violet. By BOB GOLFEN. Story moved in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
