</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) TEHRAN, Iran -- Nov. 12, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., NOV. 14
-- IRAN-JEWS-COX, 11-12 -- Benjamin Rankinkar, 18, looks over a
lesson in Talmud with two fellow students at the Abi Shami
Synagogue in the Iranian capital. Accustomed to cautious but
prosperous lives, Iranian Jews now wonder if the rules have
changed. Many consider joining relatives in North America, Europe
or Israel. (Larry Kaplow/Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) UNDATED -- Nov. 12, 1999 -- OBIT-GALIMIR-B&AMP;W, 11-12 --
Felix Galimir performing in 1992. Galimir, a violinist who was one
of the last links to the vital musical world of prewar Vienna, and
a chamber music player who was revered by several generations of
instrumentalists as a demanding and inspiring coach, died on
Wednesday at his home in Manhattan. He was 89. (New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) WASHINGTON -- Nov. 12, 1999 -- ALBRIGHT-U.N.-DUES, 11-11
-- Secretary of State Madeleine Albright during testimony before
the Senate Foreign Relations Committee in October. Albright has
told the White House that she is willing to take the political heat
from abortion rights groups if the administration compromises in
its budget talks with Congress to free up a deal to pay off nearly
$1 billion the U.S. owes the U.N. (Shana Raab /New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) FRISCO, Texas -- Nov. 12, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SAT., NOV. 13
-- CARIBBEAN-ROCKET-2-COX, 11-12 -- Beal Aerospace manufactures
large-scale space vehicles at its facility in Frisco. Plans to
