to mourners who lost friends or loved-ones in airplane crashes.
Saying only they truly understand the intense grief, numbness and
denial that come when an airliner goes down, relatives of plane
crash victims are banding together to form ``grief mentoring''
networks for those left behind in airline disasters. (Edward
Keating/New York Times Photo)
